    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your<strong> baharat</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
